Charles A. MAU et al. v. SUMMIT OIL COMPANY et al. No. 1120. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. July 20, 1934. James Donovan, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Clay & Benton and A. K. Barnes, both of Denver, Colo., and C. R. Ellery, of Cheyenne, Wyo., for appellees.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure to prosecute.
